## Dual compliance gates

Release-quality changes for this generator must pass **both** compliance gates:

| Gate | Role | Scope | Location |
|------|------|-------|----------|
| **A — OAS composition fixtures** | Spec correctness | ~15 named fixture schemas exercising every lowering rule | `openai-cpp-sdk/oas-compliance/` |
| **B — OpenAI corpus** | Scale and realism | Full generate → compile → type-inventory against the pinned OpenAI document (~891 anyOf, ~254 oneOf, ~832 nullable branches) | `openai-cpp-sdk/openai/compliance/` |

Release is blocked while either gate has non-deferred `FAIL`s.

```bash
# Run both gates sequentially:
./openai-cpp-sdk/run-dual-gates.sh

# Individual gates:
./openai-cpp-sdk/oas-compliance/gate-a.sh          # Gate A only
./openai-cpp-sdk/openai/compliance/harness.sh       # Gate B only
```

**Gate A** is OAS-only — no dependency on OpenAI type names, vendor extensions,
or patterns. A Gate A failure always indicates a spec-level codegen defect.

**Gate B** validates that the general lowering rules work at scale
on a real-world document with hundreds of union schemas, discriminators,
streaming endpoints, and multipart operations.

