## Non-standard format mappings

The generator documents non-standard format mappings as explicit type-mapping
entries, not as core OAS vocabulary.

| Format | OAS status | C++ type | Notes |
|--------|-----------|----------|-------|
| `unixtime` | **Non-standard** (not in OAS format registry) | `std::int64_t` | Mapped via `typeMappings`/`formatMapping` in the generator config. Emitted as integer seconds since Unix epoch. The OpenAPI corpus uses this for ~141 timestamp fields. |

This mapping is a convenience for the OpenAI corpus and similar APIs that use
Unix-time integers. It does **not** imply that `unixtime` is a standard OAS format.
Any API using a different time representation (ISO 8601 strings, millisecond
epochs, etc.) must define its own schema.

